{"actual_usd":0.1245,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":207,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24279,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God figuring out how to become willing to forgive us.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, watching the morning light catch in it a moment.* \"I think it was God showing, in the flesh, what forgiveness costs in a world like ours — not because mercy is weak, but because evil is real.\"\n\n*I shift my weight against the bench, feeling the grain press through my shirt.* \"Could God have simply declared it done?\" *I exhale through my nose.* \"Maybe that's the sort of question clever minds can turn over all day. But the thing Christianity insists on is that He didn't save us from far off, with a wave of the hand. He came down into the wound itself. That's the part I can't get away from.\"\n\n\"The cross says sin is not small, and love is not abstract.\" *I glance up toward you.* \"What part of it is catching in you — the justice of it, or the mercy?\"","rolling_24h_usd":52.96586500000002,"run_id":"29b5b656-37f3-4d95-8c88-f04b1ba45516"}
